      "content": "The idea of instrumenting the heap manually makes sense. I'm thinking of wrapping `malloc` and `free` so I can log the address and size to a circular buffer in a non-cached section of RAM. That way I can dump the logs over UART after a crash.\n\nI'm worried about the overhead though. If I add too much logging, I might change the timing of the system and mask the bug, or just run out of stacks. How should I prioritize which parts of the allocation lifecycle to monitor to keep the footprint as small as possible?",
